inn1.comm: bang on the money straightaway, pitches on a good length on middle and off stump, Fleming waits for it on the back foot and defends on the off side
Fierce and fast and that climbed on Fleming from a good length, he lets it go just outside the off stump and Gilchrist takes it above his head
Banged in short on leg and middle into Fleming's rib cage, 145khm, Fleming fends it to the leg side, off the glove not the bat
Pitches on a perfect length on off stump and beats Fleming for pace
on target yet again, Lee is hitting a superb length, Fleming defends on the back foot
New Zealand are away, Fleming edges one outside off stump wide of the man at second slip, far from convincing but New Zealand will take it
pitches outside off stump, angling into the left hander and moving away from him off the pitch, Fleming lets it go
left alone again outside off stump, Bracken is getting it to move aay from the left-hander quite nicely
Fleming gives Bracken the charge, he's no where near the ball and ends up fending at it and gets comprehensively beaten by the away movement
Fleming's wiser this time and lets one go outside the off stump
shot, first convincing one from Fleming this morning, that was pitched far too full and Fleming met it on the half-volley and creamed it though covers for four
good comeback from Bracken, pitched that just short of a length and drew Fleming forward, driven to mid-off
short and wide outside off stump, Astle takes a look and decides he wants nothing to do with it
shortish length outside off stump, this time Astle goes after it and gives it a real whack, Symonds dives to his left at cover and fields it with one hand, superb stuff
oh yes, a play and miss, Lee bowled that full and fast and drew Astle into the drive, the ball moved off the pitch away from the right hander and whizzed past the outside edge

caught! Lee pitched that short of a length and outside off stump, Astle waited for it and tried to cut it, his feet didn't move at all and he ended up getting a huge nick through to Gilchrist, Lee deserved a wicket, he's been outstanding today
pitches on a good length and shapes away from the right-hander, Marshall begins to play at it but pulls his bat out of the way
152kmh, full and fast angling into the right-hander, pitching on off stump and moving away off the pitch, Marhsall is beaten all ends up as he tries to drive
left alone outside the off stump, excellent length from Bracken, not allowing Fleming to come forward and not giving him the time to play back
nagging line and length outside off stump, Fleming gets his front foot forward and shoulders arms
defended on the off side, that kicked off a good length and Fleming defended it high on the bat
pitches just outside off stump and moves away from the left-hander, Fleming lets it go
and again, Fleming's being rather cautious this morning, choosing to leave a lot of deliveries
fullish ball outside offf and Fleming throws his bat at it trying to flay it through covers, the ball hits the thick outside edge and flies through point

pitches short of a length on leg and middle and angles across Fleming who doesn't know much about whats happening at the moment, he fends at it and the ball hits the top of the bat and flies over slips

Lee has another one, brilliant pace bowling, Lee pitches it on a perfect length and seams it away from the right hander off the pitch, Marhsall plays back and pokes at it, the ball kisses the outside edge and Gilchrist does the rest
full and fast on off and middle stump, Taylor meets it with a straight bat and defends back to the bowler

this one beats the outside edge, Lee pitches it short of a length, Taylor plunged his front foot forward when he should have just played back and let it go, the ball moves away from him off the pitch and beats the outside edge
Lee is cranking it up now, that was 155.5kmh, Lee let it rip outside off stump, Taylor chased it and tried to thump it through covers and was beaten
outstanding, Lee bowls thsi just short of a length and shaping away from the right-hander, Taylor fends outside the off stump but doesn't get near it
pitches on a good length outside off, Fleming lets it go
Fleming lets it go again outside off stump
hat-trick of left-alones, this one's on a perfect length and shaping away from the left-hander
a touch fuller from Bracken this time, Fleming drives but doesn't time it well, Hussey runs across from mid-off and does the fielding, no run and the pressure is inching upwards
a touch short but but it's not wide enough to cut, Fleming tries to force it past point but gets beaten
defended on the off side, Fleming's stuck in the mire at the moment, unable to gather any sort of momentum
fullish ball outside off stump, Taylor thumps it hard into the ground and to Hussey at cover, the crowd get all excited because they think its a catch
on a good length outside off stump, Taylor gets forward and drives to cover
pitches short of a length outside off stump and moves away from Taylor who plays back and pushes at it, the ball beats the outside edge like it has done so many times this morning

four leg-byes, Lee banged that short and into Taylor's body, he moved across in a hurry and tried to fend it down, the ball beat him and thudded into the thigh pad and flew wide off Gilchrist for four
fullish ball on middle and leg stump, driven to mid-on
short of a length and wide out side off stump, Taylor frees his arms and gives it an almighty thump, Clarke dives to his left at point and saves a certain boundary
driven hard back to the bowler, the ball bounces off Lee's hand and they run a single
pitches short of a length on middle stump angling across the right-hander, punched off the back foot to cover
fullish ball on middle and leg, Taylor clips it off his pads wide off Stuart clark at mid-on, they take a single
short and wide outside off stump, Fleming cuts crisply but cannot beat Michael Clarke at point
full ball angling into the pads, flicked behind square for a single

angles across the right-hander, picthes outside off stump and shapes away from the bat, Taylor pushes forward at it and gets beaten, Bracken had been getting it to swing into the right-hander until now, he's getting it to move away also
and again, impeccable bowling, picthes outside off, moves away and beats Taylor's defence

pitche sa touch too short outside off stump, Fleming stands tall on the back foot, lets the ball come to him and pierces the gap at cover point to perfection, he's timed that superbly and that would have been four if not for a superb bit of fielding from Clarke and Symonds on the fence
strays down leg side this time and the ball clips the pads and runs down to the fence for four more leg byes
sublime shot, Lee bowls it too fulla nd outside off stump, Taylor plants his foot forward and slams it through covers for four more, easily the shot of the day so far
and he goes one better! this wasn't as full as the previous one but Taylor used the width to free his arms and slash it through point, superb shot
driven back to Lee, that was timed really well but Lee got down in time to save runs, Taylor is looking really good out there
pitches on a good length on off and middle, driven to mid-on
pitches short of a length on off stump, tucks Fleming up and hits him on the thigh pad
fuller length just outside off stump, Fleming gets forward and drives to cover, he timed that rather well, just needs to find the gap
short of a length on off stump, Fleming committed himself on the front foot, found that he was early on the shot and defended on the off side
pitches short of a length outside off stump, Fleming lashes it at point where Cameron White dives full length to his right and brings off a superb save
Bracken changes his pace and beats Fleming with the slower ball
pitches on a good length on off stump, Fleming plays half forward and defends towards point
hits the McGrath length with the first ball, the batsman lets it go
shot! What a player Taylor could turn out to be, that was just short of a length just outside off stump, Taylor plays the square drive wide of Symonds at covera nd finds the fence
clever comeback, McGrath bowls that fuller and faster, Taylor lashes at it and gets beaten, he just needs to keep his composure here
banged in short on middle and leg stump, Taylor swivels and pulls down to fine leg
pitche son middle and off and moves away from the left-hander, Fleming defends on the back foot but the ball sneaks past the outside edge
fuller ball on off stump, Fleming gets forward and confidently defends to cover
Pitches on a good length on off stump, angling across the right hander, Taylor gets forward and defends
left alone outside off stump
Pitches on leg and middle, Taylor flicks off his pads down to fine leg
pitches on off stump on a good length, moves a fraction off the pitch away from the left-hander, just enough to beat the outside edge
and again, outstanding stuff from Bracken who moves it away from the bat yet again and beats Fleming
defended on the front foot
Pitches just outside off stump and cuts back sharply into Fleming who gets hit on the pad, Gilchrist dives acrobatically to his left and takes it one-handed
Pitches just outside off stump and cuts back sharply into Fleming who gets hit on the pad, Gilchrist dives acrobatically to his left and takes it one-handed
Fuller ball on middle and leg stump, Fleming leans forward and drives to mid-on for one
Pitches outside off stump and moves away, Taylor lets it go

He strikes first ball! Good length outside off stump, Fleming tries to loft it over the off side, he was not to the pitch of the ball and he hit it high on the bat to Hussey at mid-off, who takes an easy catch
Peter Fulton is the new batsman, heï¿½TMs at the non-strikerï¿½TMs end because the batsmen crossed before the catch was taken.
Good length on off stump, Taylor leans forward and drives to mid-off
Hits a good length outside off stump yet again, Taylor defends on the front foot on the off side
Fuller length on off stump, Taylor times the drives nicely but canï¿½TMt beat mid-off
Good length once again, the batsman drives to cover and Clark completes a wicket maiden in his first over
banged in short, Fulton ducks under it
pitches on a good length just outside off stump, the length draws Fulton out into the drive and the ball moves a shade away to beat the outside edge
banged in short again and Fulton spots it early, he rocks back and pulls it to the midwicket fence
defended to midwicket on the front foot
pitches on a good length on off stump, dabbed short of midwicket for a single
pitched a fraction short on middle and leg, pulled behind square for one
dropped a fraction short and Taylor latches on to it and pulls it over midwicket for four
pitche son a good length on off stump, defended on the off side
McGrath over-steps, the batsman defends on the back foot
defended to point on the back foot
pitches on a good length on off stump, defended back to the bowler on the back foot
defended to point on the back foot
excellent ball, that pitches on a good length and nips back off the seam, Fulton is late on the shot and the ball cuts him in half
short of a length ball outside off stump, the batsman has a swish at it but gets beaten

Clark gets another! Pitches short of a length on off stump, Taylor throws his bat at it and tries to heave it down the ground, he gets a lot of height on it but not the distance, Hussey back-pedals from mid-off and takes a well-judged catch
pitches short of a length outside off stump, the batsman runs it down to third man for a single
pitches a touch fuller on middle and leg stump, the batsman works it behind square leg for a single
pitches on a good length on off and middle, McMillan plays back and defends on the leg side
excellent line and length from McGrath, McMillan defends towards cover
pitches just outside off stump and cuts back into the right-hander, McMillan gets cramped for room and the ball hits the egde and drops down at his toes
pitches just outside off stump, forcing the batsman to play at it, the extra bounc eand the away movement beats the outside edge
once again the extra bounce beats McMillan, McGrath completes a maiden over
full and in the channel outside off stum, drawing the batsman forward and the away movement beatsn the bat
short of a length on off stump, Fulton gets right behind the line and defends
defended back to the bowler
pushed uppishly into covers for a single
slower ball on a good length just outside off stump, the batsman waits for it and defends to the off side
McMillan goes for broke! He moves away and charges down the track trying to heave it over the leg side, the ball hits the inside edge and crashes into his pad
defended on the off side on the back foot
whats going on here?? that pitched well outside off stump and fulton tried to turn it through leg side, the ball moved away from him and beat the edge
defended back to the bowler on the front foot
fullish ball on off stump, Fulton leans forward and caresses it through covers, Hussey gives chase and does a magnificent job of pulling it in just inside the fence
pitches on a good length and jags back into McMillan who gets cramped for room and beaten
pitches short of a length outside off stump, McMillan has a swish and it and edged it to Gilchrist, and McGrath gets his man! or does he? The umpire says not out and McMillan gets a lucky break
defended on the front foot back to the bowler
pitches full on middle and leg stump, Fulton lofts it over mid-on
pitches short of a length and jags back into McMillan who gets hit on the pad, Clark goes up in appeal but to no avail
pitches on a good length and jags back into McMillan who gets hit on the body
what a shot, audacity at its best! McMillan charges down the track to a short ball and flat bats it high and handsomely over the long off boundary
left alone outside off stump
pitches on a good length outside off stump, Fulton has a lame poke at it outside off stump and the ball beats the outside edge, Lee picks up where he left off
a touch too short and wide outside off stump, Fulton stands on the back foot and punches through covers
beaten again outside the off stump, this is becomign too easy for Australia, Lee bowls that in the channel outside off stump and McMillan fends at it as the ball fizzes past his outside edge
defended on the back foot to the off side
slower ball outside off stump, McMillan pulls his bat away at the last moment
Pitches on a good length outside off stump, McMillan shoulders arms
a touch too short outside off stump, punched off the back foot in front of point for a single
drifting on to the pads this time, flicked through square leg for one more
fired into the pads yet again, the ball runs to short fine leg for a leg bye, Gilchrist gives chase
bowled fuller and faster on off stump, defended on the off side
swept to square leg for a single
pitches on off stump and turns into middle, Fulton plays back and defends to midwicket
banged in very short outside off stump, McMillan swerves out of the way, wide called
short of a length outside off stump, McMillan doesn't play a shot and lets it go
the bouncer once again, McMillan lets it go
full ball angling into the right-hander, McMillan gets his foot forward and defends back to the bowler
short ball outside off stump, McMillan cuts hard at Clarke at point who allows a single through a rare fumble
defended on the off side on the front foot
full and fast outside off stump, Fulton shoulders arms and lets it go
Turned off the pads to short fine leg
Drifting on to the pads yet again, whipped down to fine leg for a single
The attempted faster ball slips down leg side
Defended back to the bowler
Full ball outside off stump, driven through deep cover
Driven down the ground to long-on for a single
full ball in the channel outside off stump, Fulton has a swish at it and misses
flicked off the pads to deep midwicket for two more
defended back to the bowler on the front foot
Gotcha! Fulton perishes. Short of length, outside the off stumpm it goes straight on and Fulton plays a nothing shot,  a lame push and steers it straight to Hayden at first slip.
in the zone outside off, left alone
fullish, just outside off stump, he leans forward, pushes it out to cover region
floated on the middle stump, McMillan works it to through midwicket
slips down leg side, tried to tickle it around the corner, doesn't get a touch
on the off and middle stump line, whipped past square-leg
in the channel outside of the off stump, left alone
fullish, well outside the off stump, he reaches forward and drills it through square
in the channel outside the off stump, left alone

oh ho! misfield at mid-off and it is a four. And would you believe it it was Ponting who misfielded. He is mortal after all. McMillan charged out to Clark and drilled a powerful drive straight at Ponting and the ball slips through his fingers.
outside the off stump, left alone
fullish, on the leg side, shovelled away to deep midwicket, Hussey gets across to his left and makes a good sliding stop
on the middle stump line, turned to midwicket
drifting on to the pads, McMillan tries to work it to on side, and it runs off the pads
around off stump line, punched to cover
fullish, on the leg and middle, worked to deep midwicket
short of a length ball wide outside off stump, cut down to third man for a single
short of a length again and McMillan sees the width on offer and tries to cut, he gets an edge over first slip and collects four to third man
driven to deep cover for a single
pitches on a good length and angles into McCullum who closes the face and plays it to midwicket
outstanding pick-up shot, Clark bowled that full outsie off stumpa nd McCullum gets forward and hits on the up and over extracover for a massive six
defended on the off side
strays down leg side, wide called
Symonds is bowling medium pace now and drifts that on to the pads, flicked behind square for one
Defended to midwicket on the back foot
Pushed to midwicket on the front foot
pitches on a good length just outside off stump, it angles into middle, defended to midwicket
McMillan charges down the track and backs away to make room, McGrath sees him coming and bowls the bouncer to beat the batsman
McGrath bowls another bouncer and McMillan swerves out of the way
another short ball and this time McMillan tries to pull but gets beaten

full ball this time and McMillan gets forward and crashes it through extra cover, Symonds dives full length to his right, Ponting dives full length to his left, the ball beats them both and races to the fence
short of a length ball on off stump, McMillan plays back and defends on the off side
fired down leg side, wide called, gilchrist makes a sharp save to prevent more runs
better line this time, on off and middle, driven back to the bowler on the back foot
worked off the pads behind square for a single
short of a length on off stump, McMillan tries to turn it on the leg side and gets a leading edge that beats short third man for four
worked off the pads behind square for a single
pushed short of midwicket for another single to end the over

and he's successful with his first ball! that pitched short of  alength just outside off stump, McCullum moved across his stumps and got hit on the pads, the Australians go up in appeal and the umpire agrees, that might have struck him marginally outside the line of off stump
short of a length ball on off and middle, Vettori stands tall and defends back to the bowler
defended on the off side on the back foot
slower ball outside off stump, it pitches outside off stump and angles across the left-hander, Vettori lets it go
Defended on the leg side on the back foot
Fuller ball outside off stump, Vettori jams his bat down at the last moment and collects a single wide of point
pitches just outside off stump and swings back into the left hander after it passes the batsman, left alone by Vettori
fullish length on middle and off stump, defended back to the bowler
full length outside off stump, Vettori swats it down the ground and times it well enough to get two
clever shot, Vettori waited for it outside off stump and dabbed it down to third man, Stuart Clark runs across, dives and saves one run
Defended on the off side on the back foot
drifts on to the pads, flicked through square leg for one to end the over
good length ball on off stump, defended on the off side
McMillan takes a step down and backs away to make room, Clark spots him and digs it short, McMillan tries to cut but gets beaten
superb placement, chips it straight down the ground, McGrath picks it up just inside the fence
angled behind point for a single

Vettori's clever shot wasn't so clever this time, knowing that Vettori likes to run it down to third man, Ponting stationed himself at a wide slip, Clark bowled it short of  a length outside off stump and Vettori opened the face and ran the ball straight to Ponting who took a sharp catch at face height
Clark greets him with a bouncer, Franklin takes evasive action by ducking under it
and McMillan welcomes him by thumping him through extra cover for four, powerful shot and most of the power was generated in the wrists
carved down to long on for a single, Ponting has protection in the deep now
Pitches on off stump and moves away from the left-hander, the ball kisses Franklin's edge and runs down to third man
Bracken fires in the Yorker and McMillan hurries to get his bat down in the nick of time, the ball hits the inside edge  and runs down to fine leg
Slower ball, defended to cover
another slowish ball but this time he drifts on to the pads, worked behind square on the leg side
Clark tries to find the blockhole but it ends up as a low full toss, McMillan pushes it down the ground for one
fullish length on off stump, Franklin drives to mid-off for a quick single
short of a length on middle stump, tucked off his hips on the leg side for one
bowled short of a length from wide of the crease from round the wicket, Franklin nudges it to midwicket for a single

full ball yet again, searching fror the yorker, McMillan clips the low full toss off his pads for midwicket, he scampers through for two and reaches and invaluable fifty,  he's had his luck but credit for making it count!
cheeky cheely, McMillan took a step or two down, Clark bowled it short but this time McMillan poked at it and ran it fine down to the third man fence
pitches short of a length outside off stump and angling into the left hander, Franklin waits for it and dabs it down to third man
full and wide outside off stump, McMillan makes room and slaps it back past the bowler for two runs
Franklin better be on his toes at the non-striker's end, McMillan thumps it again back past Bracken for two more to long off
clipped over midwicket for two more, McMillan is motoring along now
massive! This was always on the cards, Bracken bowls it full, McMillan gets his front foot out of the way and carts it over the fence at deep midwicket, outstanding shot
run down to third man for a single to end the over
pitches wide outside off stump and McMillan smashes it through cover for a single
fullish ball on off stump, Franklin gets to the pitch of the ball using his long reach and drives through extra cover for a single
short ball and McMillan rocks back and pulls to deep backward square leg
defended back to the bowler
Short and wide outside the left-hander's off stump, cut down to third man for two
driven off the back foot for a single to sweeper cover
pitches just outside off stump on a good length, Franklin tries to run it fine but gets more of an edge down to third man for four
pushed back to the bowler on the back foot
Full length on middle and leg stump, flicked to deep midwicket for a two
Bowled slower on a good length, Franklin waits for it and dabs it short of cover for a single
Full toss on middle stump, swung over midwicket for a hastily scampered two

McMillan tries to heave it down the ground but gets an inside edge on to the off side, he sets off for the single, Symonds sprints to the ball, picks up, turns and shies, he misses the stumps of McMillan would have been short at the non-striker's end
bowled short of a length on off stump, McMillan sways back and chips it down to third man for a single
pitches short of a length just outside off, Franklin dabs it in front of point for a single, there have been 19 scoring shots in a row now
that's number 20 and what a shot, he latched on to the length and smases it through covers, placed it perfectly and the ball scorched the turf before reaching the fence
short of a length outside off stump, Frrankin tries to pull but misses
short ball yet again and this time Franklin connects with the pull, he pulls it straight to Matthew Hayden at deep midwicket, Hayden hardly had to move and took an easy catch
McGrath tries to fire in the yorker, McMillan pushes it to cover for a single
slower ball dipping into Gillespie, defended back to the bowler on the front foot
short ball and Gillespie tries to...ummm..well I think he tried to pul, but he got his head out of the way and took evasive action in the end
banged in short again, Gillespie backs away and cuts it in the air down to third man, McMillan declines the single because he wants the strike
bouncer and McMillan ducks under it
another short ball, McMillan tries to back away and run it down to third man but gets beaten for pace
Shortish length, McMillan backs away and Lee follows him, McMillan plays a half pull shot to deep midwicket for two more
that's six, and what a shot! Lee dropped that shot and wide, McMillan freed his arms and carved that over point for maximum runs
tucked down to fine leg for a single

fast and furious, Gillespie backs away and Lee follows him with the short ball, the batsman evades it and Gilchrist  collects, he tries to affect a run out and they concedes over throws to mid-on, Lee isn't happy at all
defended on the leg side

that's the end of a pugnacious innings! McGrath bowls a full toss, McMillan tries to hoick it down the ground and skies it back to the bowler, McGrath takes a simple catch, there's a bit of confusion as to whether the full toss was above waist height, McMillan hangs around for a bit but has to go in the end
McGrath gives him a short one to say Hello! Mason swings it through midwicket for one
full ball outside off stump, Gillespie backs away to smash it but gets beaten
full ball on off and middle stump, Gillespie backs away and squeezes it through the off side for one
short ball on off and middle stump, the batsman backs away and tries to force it through the off side but doesn't make contact
tucked through midwicket for a single
pitches on a good length slanting into middle and leg, gillespie baks away far down leg side and tries to slash it through the off, he doesn't make contact
Lee oversteps in trying to find the blockhole and the batsman gets the toe end of the bat on the ball and manages to get four down to fine leg
Good length ball just outside off stump, Gillespie backs away and cuts for a single through point
fuller length on off stump, Mason stands his ground and defends back to the bowler
steered down to third man for a single
full length on off stump, Gillespie backs away and swats it to Ponting at cover
Mason chips it over extra cover for a single
full toss outside off stump, Gillespie tries to hit over the leg side but gets an outside edge down to third man
the yorker hits Gillespie on his toe, there's a half-hearted appeal for lbw but that was missing leg, they run two leg byes to third man
that's the end of that, Bracken bowls the effort ball, just a bit quicker and in the blockhole, Mason plays all around it and has his stumps re-arranged, New Zealand are bowled out for 218

inn2.comm: pitches the first one outside leg stump and that's a wide down leg side, not the start New Zealand would have wanted
pitches on leg stump again, Gilchrist works it off his pads through midwicket for a single to get off the mark
fullish length on off stump, Hayden gets forward and drives to cover
good length from Mason, he pitches that on off stump, Hayden comes forward and gets squared up and gets an outside edge to point, Mason has over-stepped though
pitches on middle and leg on a good length, Hayden plays on the back foot and defends to midwicket
pitches short of a length on middle and off, Hayden stands on the back foot and pushes to midwicket
short of a length again and tucks Hayden up on the back foot, he awkwardly fends that down on the leg side
full ball on off and middle, Hayden leans into the drive and punches it hard back to the bowler, Mason does well to get down in time, he finishes a tight first over but for the extras
he too starts with a wide down leg side, Franklin is angling the ball into gGlchrist and just strayed in line that time
full ball on off stump, Gilchrist drives uppishly between cover and mid-off, Vettori does the fielding
that's a huge wicket! Franklin bowled that very wide outside off stump and Gilchrist chased it with a full-blooded swing, it was too wide and Gilchrist only managed a thick edge through to McCullum
full ball outside off stump, Clarke jabs down at it and gets an inside edge on to pad
good length ball outside off stump, steered to point with an open face
full ball on off and middle stump, driven hard back at the bowler, Franklin plucks it out with one hand
The bouncer to finish the over, Clarke lets it go
Mason starts with a slower ball on leg stump, the ball clips Hayden's pad through to McCullum
fuller ball on off stump, Hayden leans into a good-looking off drive but hits it straight to mid-off
defended to mid-on on the front foot

Hayden goes! He drove hard and away from his body at one that was short of  alength and a touch wide, he couldn't keep it down and Ross Taylor pulled off a sharp catch, diving forward and to his left and cover
pitches on a good length in the channel outside off stump, Ponting plants his foot forward and shoulders arms
pitches just outside off stump on a goo length, Ponting shoulders arms again, that's two wickets in two overs for New Zealand
defended to covers on the back foot
fullish ball angling across the right-hander, Clarke gets forward and pushes to covers
Franklin over-steps and bowls a rank half-volley outside off stump, Clarke hammers it, absolutely hammers it to cover where Ross Taylor makes a superb save, that was hit very very hard
driven to mid-off on the front foot for  a single
hits a good length on middle and off stump, angling across Ponting from over the wicket, Ponting plays back and across and defends
fuller length and that swings into Ponting a fraction after angling across him, he gets forward and defends
defended to midwicket on the front foot
pitches outside off stump, Clarke lets it go and the ball cuts back late into the right-hander and passes close to off stump
loud shout for lbw is turned down, that pitches on middle and Clarke moves across his stumps and tries to flick, the ball beats the bat and thuds into the pad but it was slipping down leg
left alone outside off, that took off from a short length
fuller ball on off stump, Clarke gets forward and drives back at the bowler, Franklin gets down in time and gets a hand on it
good length ball on off and middle, Clarke gets forward and pushes to mid-on
poor ball, full and wide outside off stump, Clarke gets forward, reaches out for it and drives through covers for four, that's the first boundary of the innings
pitches on a good length outside off stump, Ponting lets it go
straighter line on off and midle, Ponting waits for it, plays back and defends back to the bowler
Fuller length on off stump, Ponting gets a stride in, presents a straight bat and blocks
A fraction short, Ponting seizes on the length in a trice, he swivels into position and smashes it flat and low through midwicket for four
Pushed slowly back past the stumps at the non-striker's end for a very very quick single
full ball angling across Clarke who covers the line of the stumps and lets it go
Pitches on a good length just outside off stump, Ponting sizes it up and decides to shoulder arms
